@ctiller I encountered some issues when I try to include grpc as a bazel submodule:
1. duplicated symbols, for example, `grpc_register_built_in_plugins` is defined both in `grpc_unsecure_plugin_registry.c` and `grpc_plugin_registry.c` which are both included in `grpc++_unsecure` target, there more than one such cases, see [all the hacking fix here](https://github.com/llhe/tensorflow/blob/19bf520f381b50086aadb2eb41eabfeca55d0e3e/third_party/grpc.BUILD#L58)
2. incorrect header path -- This is a actually a false alarm, I finally resolved it by deleting nanopb package from tensorflow workspace, the issue is resolved.
